emuInput.TitMainTitle: Temple 22 Restaurant and Joe's Tavern, 800 block of Brushton Avenue lined with cars, Homewood
emuInput.CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper March 29, 1958, pg. 7, reads: "Attention State Liquor Control Board - How Many More Taverns Can Homewood-Brushton Stand? Five of Brushton's Six - Among the six liquor dispensing establishments in six blocks of Brushton are...(right photo): Joe's Tavern in the 800 block of Brushton Ave. The other licensed establishment is The Honey Dew, in the 500 block.... - All Photos by Harris."
